    },
    {
      "id": "f14f0f55f39ede93ac39499bdb58e3d137a6fa32",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-12 03:30:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nFor kernels that uses i_mutex to protect .lseek, i_mutex locking is always implemented inside file system's .lseek functions. For RHEL6.3, we are taking f_lock where other file systems are taking i_mutex. However, we don't have any context switching nor nested locking inside f_lock. So I don't think it will dead lock even if we use f_lock instead of i_mutex here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
